"title": "6511: salvation, nature of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6511",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Salvation involves a change in the relationship between God and a person. Salvation includes God's adoption of believers into his family, his acceptance of them as righteous and his forgiveness of their sins. It also includes personal renewal and transformation through the work of the Holy Spirit.</p>\n<h2>Salvation as a change in status before God</h2>\n<h3>Access to God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:1-Rom5:2\">ROM 5:1–5:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:13\">EPH 2:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:16\">HEB 4:16</a></p>\n<h3>Adoption into the family of God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:12\">JHN 1:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:22-Rom8:24\">ROM 8:22–8:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:4-Gal4:7\">GAL 4:4–4:7</a></p>\n<h3>Forgiveness of sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:30-Acts5:31\">ACT 5:30–5:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps32:1-Ps32:2\">PSA 32:1–32:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:28\">MAT 26:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:43\">ACT 10:43</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:38\">ACT 13:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:7\">EPH 1:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:13\">COL 2:13</a></p>\n<h3>Heavenly citizenship</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:20-Phil3:21\">PHP 3:20–3:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:19\">EPH 2:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:1-Col3:2\">COL 3:1–3:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:22-Heb12:24\">HEB 12:22–12:24</a></p>\n<h3>Inheritance from God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:17\">ROM 8:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:12\">COL 1:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:7\">REV 21:7</a></p>\n<h3>Peace with God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:13-Eph2:17\">EPH 2:13–2:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:5\">ISA 53:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:33\">JHN 16:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:1-Rom5:2\">ROM 5:1–5:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:15\">COL 3:15</a></p>\n<h3>Righteousness in the sight of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:17\">ROM 1:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:10\">ISA 61:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:22\">ROM 3:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:3-Rom4:13\">ROM 4:3–4:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:25-Rom5:1\">ROM 4:25–5:1</a> <em>The idea of being righteous in the sight of God lies at the heart of Paul's doctrine of justification by faith</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:30\">1CO 1:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:21\">2CO 5:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:8-Phil3:9\">PHP 3:8–3:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:8\">2TI 4:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:7\">HEB 11:7</a></p>\n<h2>Salvation as a change in a person's nature</h2>\n<h3>Becoming a new creation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:17\">2CO 5:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:4\">ROM 6:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:14-Gal6:15\">GAL 6:14–6:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:15\">EPH 2:15</a></p>\n<h3>Deliverance from God's righteous condemnation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:1-Rom8:2\">ROM 8:1–8:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa50:8\">ISA 50:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:15-Rom5:17\">ROM 5:15–5:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:33-Rom8:39\">ROM 8:33–8:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:22\">COL 1:22</a></p>\n<h3>Deliverance from the power of sin and evil</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:3-Gal1:4\">GAL 1:3–1:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:14\">ROM 6:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom7:21-Rom7:25\">ROM 7:21–7:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:2-Rom8:4\">ROM 8:2–8:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:24\">1PE 2:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:5\">REV 1:5</a></p>\n<h3>Inner personal renewal</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John1:7\">1JN 1:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:1-Ps51:2\">PSA 51:1–51:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:7\">PSA 51:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:3\">HEB 1:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:19-Heb10:22\">HEB 10:19–10:22</a></p>\n<h3>New birth</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:3-John3:7\">JHN 3:3–3:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:18\">JAS 1:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:23\">1PE 1:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:9\">1JN 3:9</a></p>\n<h3>The presence of the Holy Spirit</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:10-Rom8:11\">ROM 8:10–8:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:2-Gal5:25\">GAL 5:2–5:25</a></p>",
